I've heard the 1 in 4 number before, but that is probably taken from non-excluded overlapping samples.  The real number is probably closer to 14.5% for girls and 7.2% for boys.  http://www.sciencedirect.com/science?_ob=ArticleURL&_udi=B6V7N-3SWVJJ8-6&_user=10&_rdoc=1&_fmt=&_orig=search&_sort=d&view=c&_acct=C000050221&_version=1&_urlVersion=0&_userid=10&md5=3bf4125ab05f663f306a1ca792f43398  #bibl1